<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-74-0807 </DOCNO><TEXT>The activation of carbon-hydrogen bonds by transition metals that leadsto the selective functionalization of hydrocarbons, especially alkanes,is one of the most challenging problems in organometallic chemistry.Herein, the authors report on the palladium(II)-mediated oxidation ofarenes and alkanes through a nonradical, electrophilic C-H activationpathway.</TEXT></DOC>